# Sidebar sub-navigation lists

Use this pattern for **indented lists under a main nav row** (e.g. Chief of Staff, Knowledge, Wisdom) when the design matches **Starred / Recents chat rows** but **without a star icon**.

## CSS modules (`SidebarMenu.module.css`)

| Class | Role |
|-------|------|
| **`sidebarSubNavList`** | Wrapper: column flex, `overflow: hidden`, animated `max-height` (collapsed vs expanded) |
| **`sidebarSubNavListExpanded`** | When the sub-list is open: raises `max-height` so rows are visible |
| **`sidebarSubNavRowFade`** | Staggered fade on rows; pair with inline **`--stagger`** (0-based index) and list-level **`--n`** (item count) for **0.025s** delay steps (forward on expand, reverse on collapse) |
| **`chatRow`** | Base row surface (same as chat rows) |
| **`sidebarSubNavRow`** | Adds **left indent** only: `padding: 8px 12px 8px 44px` (aligns label with parent nav text after the 20px icon + 12px gap) |
| **`chatLabel`** | Text cell: ellipsis, full typography (see below) |
| **`chatRowSelected`** | Selected row (optional) |

Do **not** put `font: inherit` on the row modifier; it overrides `.chatRow` typography.

## Typography (shared with Starred / Recents)

- **Row (`.chatRow`)**: `overflow: hidden`; `color: var(--Secondary-600, #3E4A5E)`; Inter stack; `font-size: 14px`; `font-weight: 400`; `line-height: 22px`; `letter-spacing: 0.14px`
- **Label (`.chatLabel`)**: same sizes + `overflow: hidden`; `text-overflow: ellipsis`; `white-space: nowrap`; `color: inherit` (hover uses `Secondary-700` / selected from `chatRowSelected`)

## Row structure

- One **`<button type="button">`** per row (or equivalent interactive control) with **`chatRow` + `sidebarSubNavRow` + `sidebarSubNavRowFade`** + optional **`chatRowSelected`** when using the shared expand/collapse animation.
- While the parent nav is active, keep the sub-list **mounted** (toggle only **`sidebarSubNavListExpanded`** + `aria-hidden` / `inert`) so **fade-out** can run before unmounting when switching away.
- Inner text: **`<span className={styles.chatLabel}>`** only (no star column).
- **Height**: 38px row from `.chatRow` min/max height and padding.

## Expandable nav row (chevron)

Use **`navRowExpandableSubNav`** on the nav `<button>` and **`navRowSubNavExpanded`** when the sub-list is open (chevron points up). Same pattern for Chief of Staff, Knowledge, Controls, and Wisdom.

## Reference implementation

`SidebarMenu.tsx`: expandable nav ids `chief-of-staff`, `knowledge`, `controls`, `wisdom` when the respective sub-list is expanded.
